Manufacturer of natural skincare products, Avila Naturalle Limited, has unveiled its fashion brand. According to a statement on Wednesday, the firm said it was inspired by the need to further ignite the feeling of happiness in people by offering good quality and affordable clothing that would not only meet their needs but also give a sense of class and style. The President, Avila Naturalle, Mrs Temitope Mayegun, at the grand finale of the firm’s annual distributors’ summit and excellence award, said the firm offers designs with the modern family in mind. “Avila Fashion is aiming at becoming a continental brand name that will have several branches and outlets in cities across Africa and some countries of the world. The business is also aimed at meeting the growing demand for classy yet affordable clothing whilst competing favourably with other leading brands in the African fashion industry,” she said. Mayegun noted that the new fashion brand was in furtherance to the vision of Avila Group to be a global household brand that would inspire a healthier and happier world. “Therefore, all the divisions of Avila, including the ones to come in the near future will ultimately make people the world over, live healthier and happier one way or the other,” she added. The event also witnessed the presentation of awards and special prices to its best-performing distributors nationwide.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com